[2026-03-03T06:30:08.799Z] event=response.thinking data={"content_index":0,"sequence_number":147,"text":"\nThe user is asking to count something per month based on \"first_transaction_date\". They've selected the SalesSemantic tool. However, looking at the semantic model description, I can see that the TBL_SALES table has:\n- TRANSACTION_DATE (date of transaction)\n- CREATED_AT (timestamp of record creation)\n\nBut there's no column explicitly called \"first_transaction_date\" mentioned in the semantic model. The user might be referring to:\n1. TRANSACTION_DATE (which would be the date of each transaction)\n2. CREATED_AT (timestamp when record was created)\n3. They want to calculate the first transaction date per customer and then count by month\n\nSince there's ambiguity here about what exactly to count (count of what? sales? customers? transactions?) and what field to use for the date, I should query the semantic model to get more details about available date fields and understand the data better, or I could try to make a reasonable interpretation.\n\nActually, looking at the clarification scope, I should NOT ask about basic terminologies when SQL tools are available. The user is asking for a count per month - in a sales context, this likely means counting transactions/sales per month. The \"first_transaction_date\" might be a slight misnaming of TRANSACTION_DATE, or they want to group by the month of the first transaction.\n\nLet me try the most straightforward interpretation: count sales per month based on TRANSACTION_DATE (which could be considered the \"transaction date\" for each sale). I'll issue a query to Cortex Analyst.\n"}
